article.headline: Arizona State 75, UC Riverside 59
article.story: TEMPE, Ariz. (AP) -- Bryson Krueger showed that Arizona State has some firepower behind Ike Diogu. Krueger, a transfer from Yavapai Community College, scored a season-high 23 points Sunday night, leaving Diogu to pick up 13 of his 19 points in the second half of a 75-59 win over UC Riverside. It was Krueger's second straight season high, following a 14-point performance against Fairleigh Dickinson last week. The shooting guard made five 3-pointers -- all in the first half -- in a marked improvement to his early-season starts. "I was just building off last game," Krueger said. "I'm just feeling better. I'm feeling like every time I shoot the ball it's going to go in, so having the confidence has helped me out." Coach Rob Evans said Krueger was realizing his potential. "He's getting a little more comfortable around what we're trying to do and becoming a lot more aggressive offensively, and he'll just continue to get better," Evans said. "He's got a lot of offense to add." Diogu, who scored in double figures for the 67th time in as many games, also had nine rebounds to lead the Sun Devils (7-1) to their best start since the 1992-93 team went 8-1. Rickey Porter had 17 points and Vili Morton 15 for the Highlanders (3-3). Krueger had 19 points in the first half, and the Sun Devils closed with a 12-2 run to take a 35-23 lead at the break. Krueger was 5-for-6 on 3-pointers in the half, sinking the last with 1:27 left to open the Sun Devils' first 12-point lead at 33-21. "Krueger had a nice game for them," Riverside coach John Masi said. "We identified him as a 3-point shooter, but he was able to make his perimeter shots; we weren't able to hit ours." The Highlanders opened the second half with a 13-6 run, featuring Porter's three-point play and a 3-pointer 39 seconds later that cut the deficit to 41-36 with 13:57 to go. But Diogu had a three-point play, six other free throws and a putback as the Sun Devils surged to a 63-42 lead with 7:30 remaining.
